<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-29T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-29T13:36:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23766: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vera Cruz</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Foster</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-29T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                            1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 7:16
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>British consul requests to be informed as to whether or not American
                                warships are to be sent to Vera Cruz, for the information of British
                                Admiralty.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>